The code that should initially populate the EventSupport.eventFactories
does not appear to be executed which results in any call to 
documentEvent.createEvent() to fail unless the argument is "SVGEvents"
which is added to the HashTable in a call to registerEventFactory.

In addition, their should be a entry in this table for "Events" that creates
an non-abstract version of AbstractEvent.  Xerces-J does attempt to create an 
generic event for type="Event" (they forgot the trailing "s" which I have 
reported in a bug to them).

Plus, the spec is ambiguous but I think you could make a valid case that the 
intention was for the type to be compared in a case insensitive manner (based 
on Event.type being described as case-insensitive and the values being 
identical to the feature argument to DOMImplementation.hasFeature() which is 
stated to be case-insensitive).



    /**
     * The event factories table.
     */
    protected static HashTable eventFactories = new HashTable();
    {
        eventFactories.add(MUTATION_EVENT_TYPE, new MutationEventFactory());
        eventFactories.add(MOUSE_EVENT_TYPE, new MouseEventFactory());
        eventFactories.add(UI_EVENT_TYPE, new UIEventFactory());
    }
